WEBVTT

00:08.575 --> 00:11.343
Aren't you glad
y'all came with me

00:11.345 --> 00:14.179
to see Applejack compete
in the Appleoosa Rodeo?

00:14.181 --> 00:17.616
This place is a
Cutie Mark gold mine!

00:17.618 --> 00:19.084
There's barrel racing...

00:21.087 --> 00:23.389
Roping contests...

00:23.391 --> 00:25.357
Rodeo clownin'...

00:25.359 --> 00:26.759
Steeplechase...

00:28.395 --> 00:30.396
If we can get into
some of these events,

00:30.398 --> 00:33.165
we could all three walk off
the train back in Ponyville

00:33.167 --> 00:35.734
with brand spankin'
new Cutie Marks!

00:35.736 --> 00:38.303
Wouldn't a barrel
look good here?

00:38.305 --> 00:40.072
I want a lasso!

00:40.074 --> 00:41.373
I don't know.

00:41.375 --> 00:44.810
All these events look a
little, well, dangerous.

00:44.812 --> 00:46.779
No risk, no reward.

00:46.781 --> 00:49.481
<i>Man: All right,</i>
<i>everypony listen up!</i>

00:49.483 --> 00:52.518
We need a big presence
at this here rodeo,

00:52.520 --> 00:54.686
so make yourself plenty seen!

00:54.688 --> 00:59.258
I want that low-down varmint
to know we mean business!

00:59.260 --> 01:01.360
I hope nothing
bad is going on.

01:01.362 --> 01:04.797
A Cutie-Mark-a-palooza
and a low-down varmint?

01:04.799 --> 01:08.467
This is shapin' up to be the
most exciting rodeo ever!

01:08.469 --> 01:10.302
Yeah! Come on!

01:10.304 --> 01:16.809
♪

01:20.413 --> 01:23.849
<i>♪ My little pony,</i>
<i>my little pony ♪</i>

01:23.851 --> 01:25.784
<i>♪ Aaaahhh </i>

01:25.786 --> 01:28.087
<i>♪ My little Pony </i>

01:28.089 --> 01:30.589
<i>♪ I used to wonder what</i>
<i>friendship could be. ♪</i>

01:30.591 --> 01:32.357
<i>♪ My Little Pony </i>

01:32.359 --> 01:35.094
<i>♪ Until you all shared</i>
<i>its magic with me. ♪</i>

01:35.096 --> 01:37.096
<i>♪ Big adventure! </i>
<i>♪ Tons of fun </i>

01:37.098 --> 01:39.264
<i>♪ A beautiful heart!  ♪</i>
<i>Faithful and strong! ♪</i>

01:39.266 --> 01:41.433
<i>♪ Sharing kindness </i>
<i>♪ it's an easy feat </i>

01:41.435 --> 01:43.435
<i>♪ And magic makes it</i>
<i>all complete! ♪</i>

01:43.437 --> 01:45.471
<i>♪ To have my little pony </i>

01:45.473 --> 01:49.141
<i>♪ Do you know you're all</i>
<i>my very best friends? ♪</i>

01:49.143 --> 01:51.477
<i>♪ </i>

01:56.616 --> 02:03.689
♪

02:09.796 --> 02:11.296
Woohoo!

02:11.298 --> 02:12.297
Yeehaw!

02:12.299 --> 02:13.432
That's my cousin!

02:13.434 --> 02:14.900
Go Applejack go!

02:14.902 --> 02:18.237
Phew! It's been a dog's age
since I got to compete.

02:18.239 --> 02:20.139
All the rodeos 'round
Ponyville have closed down

02:20.141 --> 02:23.842
Well, I guess having injured
kinfolk in Appleoosa

02:23.844 --> 02:25.844
sure paid off then, huh cuz?

02:25.846 --> 02:28.747
Just doin' my best to fill
your horseshoes, Braeburn.

02:28.749 --> 02:31.316
Keep tossin' like that
and I'll be out of a job!

02:31.318 --> 02:32.818
Ow-ow.

02:32.820 --> 02:34.686
Ooh. Sorry.

02:34.688 --> 02:37.556
Say, where's my sister
and her friends?

02:37.558 --> 02:39.925
Uh-oh, gee I, uh...

02:39.927 --> 02:42.461
I guess I got so caught up
watching you that I--

02:42.463 --> 02:44.463
You said you'd keep an
eye on those fillies!

02:44.465 --> 02:47.166
How am I supposed to focus on
practicing if you're not gonna--

02:47.168 --> 02:48.433
There they are!

02:48.435 --> 02:50.269
Right where I
left 'em.

02:52.505 --> 02:53.906
Aw, don't be mad.

02:53.908 --> 02:56.375
Ouch.

02:56.377 --> 02:57.809
My foreleg!

02:57.811 --> 03:00.212
Hurts so much.

03:00.214 --> 03:02.447
[giggles]

03:02.449 --> 03:04.950
Y'all can't go running
off like that, y'hear?

03:04.952 --> 03:07.719
Backstage at a rodeo
ain't no kinda playground.

03:07.721 --> 03:10.789
Sorry, Applejack. We
won't wander off again.

03:11.724 --> 03:14.526
But, uh, speakin' of the rodeo,

03:14.528 --> 03:16.628
what would you say about
me and the Crusaders

03:16.630 --> 03:20.899
maybe competin' in one teensy
weensy little event or three?

03:20.901 --> 03:22.334
Look out!

03:22.336 --> 03:25.537
♪

03:25.539 --> 03:26.538
[fearful cries]

03:26.540 --> 03:28.307
[crash]

03:31.544 --> 03:33.745
Applejack: What the
hay just happened?

03:33.747 --> 03:35.347
You fillies all right?

03:35.349 --> 03:36.548
Uh-huh.

03:36.550 --> 03:38.717
Sugar and Saltlicks!

03:38.719 --> 03:41.286
Well, I'll be...

03:41.288 --> 03:42.554
What is it, Sheriff?

03:45.959 --> 03:47.759
Is it him?

03:47.761 --> 03:50.462
Ain't no doubt.

03:50.464 --> 03:52.364
It's Trouble Shoes.

03:52.366 --> 03:58.570
<i>♪ [harmonica] </i>

04:02.408 --> 04:05.877
[concerned chatter]

04:05.879 --> 04:08.880
Woman: Is it true? Is
Trouble Shoes here?

04:08.882 --> 04:12.651
Man: You ain't gonna shut
down the rodeo, are ya?

04:12.653 --> 04:16.922
All right now, I called for
a meetin', not a mob scene.

04:18.791 --> 04:22.628
Now as many of you know, the
Equestria rodeo circuit

04:22.630 --> 04:27.633
has been plagued by the dirty
dealings of a notorious outlaw.

04:27.635 --> 04:30.836
He knocked barrels every which
way at the Hoof City Rodeo!

04:30.838 --> 04:32.904
Nearly crushed my Aunt Bay Mare!

04:32.906 --> 04:37.743
He sabotaged the steer
pen at Pinto Creek Rodeo,

04:37.745 --> 04:39.678
settin' off such a stampede

04:39.680 --> 04:42.514
they cancelled the
whole dadgum thing!

04:42.516 --> 04:44.516
Now, Now.

04:44.518 --> 04:46.952
It's true, we had an
incident this mornin'

04:46.954 --> 04:49.454
at our own Appleoosa rodeo.

04:49.456 --> 04:52.391
Hay bale stack came
down pretty near on top

04:52.393 --> 04:54.326
of three little fillies.

04:54.328 --> 04:57.562
I examined them
hoofprints myself, and...

04:57.564 --> 05:00.399
It was Trouble Shoes, all right.

05:00.401 --> 05:01.767
[everyone gasps]

05:01.769 --> 05:04.569
I reckon I oughta
cancel this rodeo

05:04.571 --> 05:07.306
like all the others done...

05:07.308 --> 05:10.309
But daghoofit, this
has gone far enough!

05:10.311 --> 05:11.977
We'll double the patrols!

05:11.979 --> 05:14.813
This rodeo will go on!

05:14.815 --> 05:18.350
Appleoosa ain't
gonna be intimidated!

05:18.352 --> 05:20.786
[cheers]

05:20.788 --> 05:26.825
So, uh, Applejack, about me and
my pals competin' in the rodeo.

05:29.562 --> 05:32.864
Apple Bloom: Don't
send us home! It's not fair!

05:32.866 --> 05:34.766
Now quit your
belly-aching.

05:34.768 --> 05:38.670
I can't have y'all around here
with some outlaw on the loose.

05:38.672 --> 05:42.441
Aw, maybe I oughta call
it quits and go home too.

05:42.443 --> 05:43.975
No, you can't!

05:43.977 --> 05:47.879
This rodeo is important to
Appleoosa and with you in there,

05:47.881 --> 05:50.048
we got a real shot at winnin'.

05:50.050 --> 05:52.117
Come on, now, you head
on back to practice

05:52.119 --> 05:54.086
and don't worry none
about these three.

05:54.088 --> 05:55.954
I won't let 'em
outta my sight.

05:55.956 --> 05:57.489
[door closes]

06:00.026 --> 06:01.126
Ya hear?

06:01.128 --> 06:03.662
Y'all ain't leavin' my sight.

06:09.635 --> 06:13.905
[snoring]

06:19.712 --> 06:22.614
I thought we weren't
going to wander off again.

06:22.616 --> 06:27.452
We know exactly where we're
headed: to find Trouble Shoes.

06:27.454 --> 06:29.788
But isn't he a
dangerous criminal?

06:29.790 --> 06:32.891
We only need to find him; we
don't need to capture him.

06:32.893 --> 06:34.726
The sheriff can handle that.

06:34.728 --> 06:37.863
And once he's in jail, we'll
be competing, and then it's...

06:37.865 --> 06:39.431
...Cutie Mark city!

06:43.970 --> 06:46.171
Worst idea ever.

06:49.041 --> 06:50.142
[hooting]

06:50.144 --> 06:57.416
♪

06:57.950 --> 06:59.851
It's another giant hoofprint!

06:59.853 --> 07:03.121
Do either of you have
any idea where we are?

07:03.123 --> 07:05.023
[thunderclap]

07:08.027 --> 07:11.630
Uh, maybe we should head
back and try again later.

07:11.632 --> 07:13.765
Come on, before
we lose the trail!

07:17.170 --> 07:18.637
[thunderclap]

07:18.639 --> 07:19.638
[squeal]

07:26.746 --> 07:29.448
Come on, we've
gone far enough!

07:29.450 --> 07:30.715
It's time to
go back!

07:30.717 --> 07:33.118
The rain is only getting
worse, Apple Bloom.

07:33.120 --> 07:34.619
Let's come
back tomorrow.

07:36.689 --> 07:38.156
Maybe y'all are right.

07:38.158 --> 07:40.592
So how do we get back?

07:40.594 --> 07:42.894
You mean you
don't know?

07:42.896 --> 07:44.162
[crack of thunder]

07:48.134 --> 07:50.168
Good job, y'all.

07:50.170 --> 07:52.838
I know they need lots of
mud for the rodeo tomorrow,

07:52.840 --> 07:55.674
but I wish they woulda warned
us about this rainstorm.

07:55.676 --> 07:57.709
[horse whinny outside]

07:57.711 --> 07:59.110
Braeburn?

07:59.112 --> 08:00.812
Where are the girls?

08:00.814 --> 08:03.081
Heh heh.

08:03.083 --> 08:04.783
Applejack: WHAT?

08:09.021 --> 08:12.757
<i>♪ [honky tonk piano] </i>

08:12.759 --> 08:15.060
Fished. My. Wish.

08:15.062 --> 08:17.829
Gol-dang nab it!

08:17.831 --> 08:18.697
[clunk]

08:18.699 --> 08:21.233
Sheriff Silverstar!
You gotta help!

08:21.235 --> 08:22.534
My sister's gone!

08:22.536 --> 08:23.902
And her friends, too!

08:23.904 --> 08:26.738
I've searched and searched
but no sign of 'em anywhere.

08:26.740 --> 08:28.540
It must've been
Trouble Shoes!

08:28.542 --> 08:30.575
Now hold on there.

08:30.577 --> 08:33.745
Trouble Shoes done a lot
of bad things in his day,

08:33.747 --> 08:35.580
but nothin' like that.

08:35.582 --> 08:37.215
You really want to
take that chance?

08:39.285 --> 08:40.652
Come on, y'all!

08:40.654 --> 08:41.753
Let's ride!

08:44.624 --> 08:47.225
You sure about
this, Scootaloo?

08:47.227 --> 08:51.062
I thought I was,
but now I'm not.

08:51.064 --> 08:54.933
So I pretty much got us
completely and totally lost.

08:54.935 --> 08:57.836
How could this
get any worse?

08:57.838 --> 08:58.803
[rumbling]

08:58.805 --> 09:00.872
[screams]

09:05.645 --> 09:07.145
We gotta get out
of this rain.

09:07.147 --> 09:09.848
There's no tellin' how
long this storm could last.

09:09.850 --> 09:10.782
Look!

09:12.218 --> 09:13.919
Apple Bloom: It looks abandoned.

09:13.921 --> 09:16.321
Let's go see if we can find
some blankets or somethin'.

09:22.795 --> 09:23.862
<i>♪ [eerie] </i>

09:29.902 --> 09:31.136
♪

09:31.138 --> 09:37.075
[footsteps]

09:37.077 --> 09:40.812
♪

09:40.814 --> 09:42.347
[scream]

09:42.349 --> 09:43.915
[male scream]

09:43.917 --> 09:45.016
[crashing]

09:45.018 --> 09:46.918
Ow!

09:46.920 --> 09:48.887
Whoa!

09:48.889 --> 09:50.288
[crashing]

09:50.290 --> 09:52.891
[clatter]

09:58.864 --> 10:00.765
Hello?

10:00.767 --> 10:02.067
You all right?

10:02.902 --> 10:04.269
Surely.

10:04.271 --> 10:05.737
We didn't mean no harm.

10:05.739 --> 10:07.906
We just came in to
get out of the rain.

10:07.908 --> 10:10.275
Had some hot cider
cooking in the kitchen.

10:10.277 --> 10:11.810
Doubt it survived.

10:13.279 --> 10:14.779
[clang]

10:14.781 --> 10:16.815
I ain't gonna rise
to greet y'all.

10:16.817 --> 10:18.917
Awfully rude I reckon,
but as you can see

10:18.919 --> 10:20.685
I'm the fresh casualty of an

10:20.687 --> 10:23.388
unusually unfortunate
circumstance.

10:23.390 --> 10:25.824
My lot in life, I s'pose.

10:25.826 --> 10:27.092
Are you...

10:27.094 --> 10:28.660
Trouble Shoes?

10:28.662 --> 10:30.195
That's me.

10:30.197 --> 10:32.631
Wh-what are you doing?

10:32.633 --> 10:33.898
I'm gonna unwrap him.

10:35.167 --> 10:36.301
You can't do that.

10:36.303 --> 10:37.902
That's Trouble Shoes!

10:37.904 --> 10:39.804
Aw, he don't seem so bad.

10:46.145 --> 10:47.979
A'course guests would arrive

10:47.981 --> 10:50.348
while I ain't got
no pie to offer.

10:50.350 --> 10:54.386
Score s'more misfortune
points for ol' Trouble Shoes.

10:54.388 --> 10:56.955
Whoa!

10:56.957 --> 10:58.123
[crash]

10:58.125 --> 11:01.026
[bonk bonk bonk]

11:05.798 --> 11:06.898
Typical.

11:06.900 --> 11:09.334
Bad luck never rests.

11:09.336 --> 11:11.102
Apple Bloom: You sure
that's bad luck?

11:11.104 --> 11:14.773
Seems like maybe you're
just a little, um...

11:14.775 --> 11:16.107
klutzy?

11:16.109 --> 11:17.742
Tell that to the flank!

11:17.744 --> 11:19.077
Upside down horseshoe.

11:19.079 --> 11:20.912
Bad luck.

11:20.914 --> 11:24.315
Follows me wherever I go
like sour on old milk.

11:24.317 --> 11:26.685
Y'all best vamoose a'fore
my bad luck rubs off

11:26.687 --> 11:27.919
and sticks to y'all.

11:27.921 --> 11:29.120
Get along.

11:29.122 --> 11:30.121
Skedaddle.

11:31.824 --> 11:33.858
Amskray!

11:33.860 --> 11:37.862
Um...we don't really know
the way back to Appleoosa.

11:37.864 --> 11:40.098
But a'course I do.

11:40.100 --> 11:42.467
Wouldn't ya know
it, my lucky day.

11:45.204 --> 11:48.073
It's actually kinda sweet of
him to help us out like this.

11:48.075 --> 11:51.409
What do we do if he takes
us back to Appleoosa

11:51.411 --> 11:53.078
and the Sheriff arrests him?

11:53.080 --> 11:54.879
If I get a Cutie Mark for that,

11:54.881 --> 11:56.848
I'll feel guilty
every time I see it.

11:58.417 --> 12:01.786
Say there, Trouble Shoes, you
might not want to take us

12:01.788 --> 12:04.189
all the way back to Appleoosa.

12:04.191 --> 12:06.224
The Sheriff sorta has
it in his mind that

12:06.226 --> 12:09.360
you're a no good outlaw lookin'
to shut down the rodeo.

12:09.362 --> 12:11.229
My kinda luck he'd think that.

12:11.231 --> 12:12.731
But...

12:12.733 --> 12:14.199
is it true?

12:14.201 --> 12:16.201
Y'all like stories?

12:16.203 --> 12:17.769
Mm hm.

12:17.771 --> 12:19.370
Just my luck.

12:19.372 --> 12:21.206
I was hopin' you'd say no.

12:23.410 --> 12:28.213
<i>I wanted to be a rodeo</i>
<i>star somethin' fierce,</i>

12:28.215 --> 12:30.815
<i>but I just didn't seem</i>
<i>to have a knack for it.</i>

12:31.417 --> 12:32.417
[clang]

12:32.419 --> 12:33.418
Whoa!

12:33.420 --> 12:34.786
[laughter)

12:38.524 --> 12:39.891
Oh!

12:39.893 --> 12:41.459
[laughter]

12:41.461 --> 12:43.962
I practiced and practiced and...

12:43.964 --> 12:45.897
Whoa!

12:45.899 --> 12:48.133
<i>...and finally I</i>
<i>wrangled up the guts</i>

12:48.135 --> 12:50.502
<i>to audition for</i>
<i>rodeo school.</i>

12:50.504 --> 12:52.303
Right in middle of that tryout,

12:52.305 --> 12:54.873
<i>I knew I was doin'</i>
<i>what I was meant to.</i>

12:54.875 --> 12:56.541
<i>And wouldn't ya know it?</i>

12:56.543 --> 12:59.144
<i>In a flash comes</i>
<i>this here Cutie Mark.</i>

13:01.213 --> 13:02.347
[crash]

13:02.349 --> 13:08.219
[laughter from judges]

13:08.221 --> 13:11.356
<i>I can still remember</i>
<i>them judges laughin'.</i>

13:11.358 --> 13:13.925
<i>I didn't even finish my</i>
<i>routine 'cause right then</i>

13:13.927 --> 13:16.461
<i>I knew bad luck was my fate.</i>

13:17.797 --> 13:21.166
<i>That fire for rodeo'in</i>
<i>never did leave me, though.</i>

13:21.168 --> 13:24.135
<i>I couldn't keep away from 'em.</i>

13:24.137 --> 13:27.539
<i>So I'd sneak down and have a</i>
<i>look and wouldn't ya know it,</i>

13:27.541 --> 13:30.041
[crash]

13:30.043 --> 13:33.545
<i>bad luck would strike again.</i>

13:33.547 --> 13:37.182
<i>Just my lot in life, I reckon.</i>

13:37.184 --> 13:38.983
Poor Trouble Shoes.

13:38.985 --> 13:40.385
I can't believe
those mean judges

13:40.387 --> 13:42.287
would laugh at
him like that.

13:42.289 --> 13:43.421
Don't ya see?

13:43.423 --> 13:45.256
They weren't
laughing at him;

13:45.258 --> 13:47.325
they were just
enjoyin' the show!

13:47.327 --> 13:48.526
What are you saying?

13:48.528 --> 13:53.264
If we saw a rodeo clown doin'
what he did back in that shack,

13:53.266 --> 13:55.433
we'd think he was the greatest!

13:55.435 --> 14:00.405
He could still be in rodeos,
just not the way he thought.

14:00.407 --> 14:03.541
So he's been looking at his
Cutie Mark wrong the whole time!

14:03.543 --> 14:05.243
It's not bad luck, it's--

14:05.245 --> 14:06.344
Gotcha!

14:09.215 --> 14:11.349
Just my luck.

14:11.351 --> 14:14.853
Trouble Shoes, you're under
arrest for vandalizin'

14:14.855 --> 14:17.188
the property and peace of mind

14:17.190 --> 14:20.325
of the good, rodeo-lovin'
ponies of Equestria,

14:20.327 --> 14:25.063
not to mention fillynappin'
and generalized mayhem.

14:25.065 --> 14:26.297
Wait!

14:26.299 --> 14:28.333
Braeburn, get these
fillies someplace safe.

14:28.335 --> 14:29.467
Wait! No!

14:29.469 --> 14:31.102
Listen, Applejack!

14:31.104 --> 14:32.503
All three fillies: No!

14:38.544 --> 14:40.378
<i>Apple Bloom: But Trouble</i>
<i>Shoes isn't the menace</i>

14:40.380 --> 14:42.113
everypony thinks!

14:42.115 --> 14:44.048
Sakes alive,
what's with you?

14:44.050 --> 14:47.285
Why in tarnation would you want
me to help get him out of jail

14:47.287 --> 14:50.255
when he's the one who ran
off with y'all to begin with?

14:50.257 --> 14:52.090
Now if y'all excuse me,

14:52.092 --> 14:55.894
I'm off to win the Appleoosa
Rodeo Hay Bale Monster Stack!

14:55.896 --> 14:57.929
Um... Applejack?

14:57.931 --> 14:59.030
[door closes]

15:04.203 --> 15:06.905
[sigh] Well, at least
I get me a view

15:06.907 --> 15:10.441
of one small corner
of the rodeo.

15:10.443 --> 15:11.442
[thud]

15:11.444 --> 15:12.677
Figures.

15:12.679 --> 15:18.516
Aw, come on now, Trouble Shoes,
I'm runnin' out of mattresses!

15:18.518 --> 15:25.590
♪

15:35.335 --> 15:38.970
you're about to miss the
Hay Bale Monster Stack!

15:38.972 --> 15:40.939
Jiminy! That startin' already?

15:45.611 --> 15:49.147
Let's go, Trouble Shoes;
this here's a jailbreak!

15:49.149 --> 15:50.581
Ain't no need.

15:50.583 --> 15:54.385
Can hear the rodeo just
fine from this vantage.

15:54.387 --> 15:56.955
But we've got a plan to
help you live your dream!

15:56.957 --> 15:59.590
Listen, y'all, I'm
a known criminal.

15:59.592 --> 16:02.493
How you proposin' on
gettin' me into a rodeo?

16:02.495 --> 16:03.494
[clunk]

16:05.130 --> 16:12.070
[cheering]

16:12.072 --> 16:14.472
Woohoo!
You can do it!
Go Applejack!

16:14.474 --> 16:18.176
Well? How do I look?

16:18.178 --> 16:20.244
[giggles]

16:25.317 --> 16:27.452
Come on, now,
stack them bales!

16:27.454 --> 16:28.720
Woohoo!

16:28.722 --> 16:35.994
♪

16:36.228 --> 16:37.228
Crowd: Whoa!

16:44.503 --> 16:46.604
[cheering]

16:46.606 --> 16:49.374
That's my sister!

16:49.376 --> 16:53.077
<i>♪ [circus theme] </i>

16:53.079 --> 16:55.580
[laughter]

16:55.582 --> 16:58.049
OK now Trouble
Shoes. You're on!

16:58.051 --> 16:59.450
Say what?

16:59.452 --> 17:04.088
I may be dressed like one,
but I ain't no rodeo clown.

17:04.090 --> 17:07.158
You got your Cutie Mark
all wrong, Trouble Shoes.

17:07.160 --> 17:09.093
You were born to entertain!

17:09.095 --> 17:12.063
You got a gift for makin'
folks laugh, don't you?

17:12.065 --> 17:14.632
But my Cutie Mark's an
upside down horseshoe.

17:14.634 --> 17:16.634
And that means bad luck!

17:16.636 --> 17:18.803
That all depends on
how you look at it.

17:18.805 --> 17:21.539
You always wanted to be a
part of the rodeo, right?

17:21.541 --> 17:24.108
Well, now's your chance.

17:24.110 --> 17:31.182
♪

17:34.386 --> 17:35.453
Go on!

17:38.090 --> 17:39.090
Whoa!

17:39.092 --> 17:40.091
Oof!

17:40.093 --> 17:44.228
[laughter]

17:44.230 --> 17:45.630
[encouraging shouts]

17:47.366 --> 17:48.533
There y'all are.

17:48.535 --> 17:50.468
How 'bout your
big sis, huh?

17:52.704 --> 17:54.072
Yeah, way to go.

17:56.809 --> 17:59.210
Since when are y'all
so into rodeo clowns?

17:59.212 --> 18:06.284
♪

18:07.719 --> 18:11.722
[laughter]

18:11.724 --> 18:16.327
♪

18:16.329 --> 18:18.763
Just leave me be, Cutie Mark.

18:18.765 --> 18:23.434
♪

18:23.436 --> 18:26.270
I aim to clear that there hoop.

18:26.272 --> 18:28.106
[screaming laughter]

18:28.108 --> 18:29.607
[crash]

18:29.609 --> 18:33.845
[laughter]

18:33.847 --> 18:35.680
Come on now!

18:35.682 --> 18:39.417
[grunts]

18:39.419 --> 18:41.686
[laughter]

18:52.664 --> 18:55.600
[hooting laughter]

18:55.602 --> 18:58.269
That's the best rodeo
clown I ever seen!

18:58.271 --> 18:59.470
Ha ha ha!

18:59.472 --> 19:01.472
[laughter]

19:14.720 --> 19:16.220
[gasp]

19:16.222 --> 19:18.322
Trouble Shoes!

19:18.324 --> 19:19.490
What the hay?

19:19.492 --> 19:21.292
He escaped from
jail!

19:21.294 --> 19:23.728
Ruinin' another
rodeo!

19:23.730 --> 19:25.229
Let's get 'im!

19:25.231 --> 19:27.465
[angry shouts]

19:27.467 --> 19:28.466
Wait, y'all!

19:28.468 --> 19:30.501
He ain't what you think he is!

19:30.503 --> 19:31.869
Stand aside, young 'uns.

19:31.871 --> 19:34.639
This one's goin'
back to jail.

19:34.641 --> 19:37.341
But he never wanted
to ruin any rodeos!

19:37.343 --> 19:39.210
Those were just bad accidents.

19:39.212 --> 19:41.445
Sweetie Belle, what're
you talkin' about?

19:41.447 --> 19:44.315
Trouble Shoes has a gift
for making ponies laugh.

19:44.317 --> 19:47.318
He's maybe the best
rodeo clown I ever seen.

19:47.320 --> 19:50.354
That's true, he
is awful funny.

19:50.356 --> 19:51.956
He thought his Cutie
Mark was tellin' him

19:51.958 --> 19:53.691
to keep away from rodeos,

19:53.693 --> 19:57.228
but deep inside he knew that's
where he was meant to be.

19:57.230 --> 19:58.829
He just didn't
know how to do it.

19:58.831 --> 20:01.799
[murmurs]

20:01.801 --> 20:03.868
What she says is true.

20:03.870 --> 20:07.438
This here, entertainin'
y'all with my klutzin',

20:07.440 --> 20:09.907
that's what I'm
s'posed to be doin'.

20:09.909 --> 20:11.576
I know it now.

20:11.578 --> 20:14.312
I didn't mean no harm, honest!

20:14.314 --> 20:17.848
I just ain't never loved nothin'
like I love the rodeo.

20:17.850 --> 20:22.954
So I kept on sneakin' back and
makin' a big ol' mess a' things.

20:22.956 --> 20:27.391
Turns out I was just lookin'
at my Cutie Mark all wrong.

20:27.393 --> 20:31.862
That may be so, Trouble Shoes,
but you still gotta face charges

20:31.864 --> 20:33.764
for the problems you caused.

20:33.766 --> 20:37.735
If I done wrong, I'll see to
it that I take my medicine

20:37.737 --> 20:39.604
and square my accounts.

20:39.606 --> 20:42.873
Truth be told, we could
understand all the trouble

20:42.875 --> 20:44.809
with the rodeos.

20:44.811 --> 20:47.678
But why'd ya have to run off
with these here littl'uns

20:47.680 --> 20:49.380
last night?

20:49.382 --> 20:51.582
Uh... yeah, about that...

20:57.689 --> 21:00.491
You really want us to clean
up all this mess

21:00.493 --> 21:02.260
Trouble Shoes made?

21:02.262 --> 21:04.262
Maybe it'll teach you
not to go wanderin' off

21:04.264 --> 21:05.930
after I say not to.

21:05.932 --> 21:09.367
Ain't it bad enough that you
get to go back to Ponyville

21:09.369 --> 21:11.936
with a shiny trophy and
all we're bringin' back

21:11.938 --> 21:14.672
is these same old
blank flanks?

21:14.674 --> 21:17.341
Y'all helped Trouble Shoes
realize what his Cutie Mark

21:17.343 --> 21:18.709
really means.

21:18.711 --> 21:21.979
Ain't that a nice feeling
you can take back with ya?

21:21.981 --> 21:24.715
I guess we did make
things a little better.

21:24.717 --> 21:26.517
Does feel kinda nice.

21:26.519 --> 21:28.452
So, we can stop now?

21:28.454 --> 21:29.920
Nope.

21:34.593 --> 21:36.661
<i>♪ My Little Pony </i>

21:38.864 --> 21:40.931
<i>♪ My Little Pony </i>

21:51.810 --> 21:53.911
<i>♪ My Little Pony </i>

21:53.913 --> 21:57.948
<i>♪ friends </i>
